00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:03.280
in your brain today are structurally different

344
00:12:03.280 --> 00:12:04.840
than they were five years ago.

345
00:12:04.840 --> 00:12:07.880
Your experiences, your learning, your environment,

346
00:12:07.880 --> 00:12:10.880
they have literally rewired the physical connections.

347
00:12:11.880 --> 00:12:13.960
Okay, here's where it gets really interesting.

348
00:12:13.960 --> 00:12:16.640
When you take everything we've just discussed,

349
00:12:16.720 --> 00:12:20.560
the psychological meaning, the neurobiological mechanisms,

350
00:12:20.560 --> 00:12:24.120
the data trade-offs, the physical rewiring over time,

351
00:12:24.120 --> 00:12:27.000
and you apply it to major human struggles,

352
00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:29.040
it totally changes how we approach things.

353
00:12:29.040 --> 00:12:31.720
It changes everything about treatment and understanding.

354
00:12:31.720 --> 00:12:32.600
Yeah.

355
00:12:32.600 --> 00:12:35.720
Let's look at fear and severe anxiety as an example.

356
00:12:35.720 --> 00:12:37.240
Fear is a brilliant example

